@node "STATES-A"
    (1) @{"ALABAMA"LINK ALABAMA}
    (2) @{"ALASKA"LINK ALASKA}
    (3) @{"ARIZONA"LINK ARIZONA}
    (4) @{"ARKANSAS"LINK ARKANSAS}
@endnode

@node "ALABAMA"
                                  @{u}ALABAMA@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Montgomery.    
POPULATION. 4136,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 Daylight saving time is observed from the first Sunday
            in April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put 
            forward one hour, changing at 0200 hours local time.
THE STATE.  Alabama offers mountains, lakes, caverns, woodland and beaches.
            Birmingham is the largest city and cultural centre. Attractions
            include the new civic sports and arts centre and the
            Birmingham Museum of Art. Other tourist destinations include
            the The Huntville Space and Rocket; The Russel Cave National
            Monument; historic Montgomery; and Mobile, a major seaport and
            resort area on the Gulf Coast. 
@endnode

@node  "ALASKA"                   @{u}ALASKA@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Juneau.

POPULATION. 587,000.
LOCATION.   North West United States, of the coast of Western Canada.
TIME.       GMT-9,east of W169° 30'; GMT-10, west of W169° 30' (the
            Aleutian Islands). Daylight saving time time is observed from
            the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks
            are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 hours local time.
THE STATE.  The largest State in the USA. Alaska is a land of glaciers,
            rivers, waterfalls, fjords, forests, tundra and meadows.
            Anchorage is the largest city. Alaskan attractions include
            Denali National Park, Kenai Peninsula, Alyeska ski area,
            Chugach National Forest, Portage Glacier, Pribilof Islands and
            Juneau the State capital and historic gold-mining city. Mount
            McKinley at 6194 m (20,320 ft) is the highest mountain in North
            America.
@endnode

@node  "ARIZONA"
                                  @{u}ARIZONA@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Phoenix.
POPULATION. 3,832,000.
LOCATION.   Western United States.
TIME.       GMT-7 Daylight saving is not observed in Arizona.
THE STATE.  Arizona has spectacular scenery, including arid plateaux,
            mountains and broad desert plains. It contains the famous Grand
            Canyon, Painted Desert and Petrified Forest National Parks. 
            Phoenix is the largest city in the State, shares borders with
            Scottsdale, the primary resort destination in Arizona. Both
            cities have a variety of accommodation and attractions, unique
            shopping,fine art galleries and many cultural events. Other
            State attractions include Tuscan, the second largest city;
            Saguaro National Monument; Arizona-Sonora Desert Museum;
            Kaibab Forest. Monument Valley Navajo Tribal Park; Hoover Dam;
            Montezuma Castle; and Tombstone, site of the infamous 
            shoot-out at the OK Corral. 
            USA Gateways @{"ARIZONA-GATEWAY" LINK ARIZONA-GATEWAY} 
@endnode

@node "ARIZONA-GATEWAY"     
                             @{u}ARIZONA GATEWAY@{uu}


Arizona including Phoenix, gateway to the southwestern States
of Arizona, New Mexico, Colorado, Utah and Nevada and the
western Pacific State of California.
            
CLIMATE: Warm and comfortable all year round, ranging from refreshing 
breezes in the mountains to hot temperatures in the desert.

CLOTHING: Lightweight cotton clothing for all seasons, with a wrap for
cool nights. warmer clothing is needed in the mountains, especially in the
ski areas.

AIR TRAVEL: From Phoenix to Atlanta is 3 hours 30 minutes. to Chicago is 
3 hours 30 minutes, to Los Angeles is 2 hours, to Miami is 4 hours and to
New York is 4 hours.
@endnode

@node "ARKANSAS"
                                  @{u}ARKANSAS@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Little Rock.
POPULATION. 2,399,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 Daylight saving time is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward one
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  A varied landscape of plains, mountains, forests, rivers,
            cattle farms, industrial centres and oil wells. It's many lakes
            are among the chief tourist attractions. Others include The Hot
            Springs National Park; Blanchard Spring Caverns; Buffalo River;
            Crater of Diamonds State Park; Eureka Springs, a town built
            into the mountainside; and Mountain View, the Ozark Mountain
            folk centre. Little Rock, one of the State's earliest
            settlements, contains parks, museums and arts centres. Bill
            Clinton was Governor of Little Rock Arkansas before becoming
            President.
@endnode

@node "STATES-C"
    (1) @{"CALIFORNIA"LINK CALIFORNIA}
    (2) @{"COLORADO"LINK COLORADO}
    (3) @{"CONNECTICUT"LINK CONNECTICUT}
@endnode

@node "CALIFORNIA"
                                  @{u}CALIFORNIA@{uu}
CAPITAL.    Sacramento.
POPULATION. 30,867,000.
LOCATION.   Western United States.
TIME.       GMT-8 Daylight saving time is observed from the first Sunday 
            in April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward
            one hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.

THE STATE. Known as the`Golden State' because of it's sunny climate and 
           the discovery of gold in pioneering days, California is a
           mixture of beaches, mountains, rugged coastline, Hollywood
           glamour, desert, woodland and orchard. The most popular State
           in the USA, it's  Major tourist destinations include Los 
           Angeles,San Francisco  and San Diego, the lush resorts of 
           Santa Barbara and Palm Springs and the artists'communities of 
           Laguna Beach and Mendocino.
           USA Gateways @{"CALIFORNIA-GATEWAY" LINK CALIFORNIA-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "CALIFORNIA-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}CALIFORNIA GATEWAY@{uu}


California including Los Angeles and San Francisco, gateway to the
West(Pacific) coast, Nevada, Oregon and Arizona.

CLIMATE: Summers are hot whilst winters are mild with wetter weather.

CLOTHING: Lightweights during the summer, with warmer wear during the
cooler winter months.

AIR TRAVEL: From Los Angeles to London is 10 hours 15 minutes. From San
Francisco to London is 12 hours 10 minutes. Plus USA internal domestic
flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node  "COLORADO"
                                  @{u}COLORADO@{uu}
CAPITAL.    Denver.
POPULATION. 3,470,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-7 Daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in 
            April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward 
            one hour,changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Colorado stands high up in the famous Rocky Mountains and
            offers National Parks, forests, gold-rush ghost towns, ancient
            Indian temples and fine ski resorts. Denver contains many
            museums, parks, gardens and a restored Victorian square. State
            attractions include Colorado Springs; Pike's Peak; The Rocky
            Mountain and Mesa Verde National Parks; Black Canyon and the
            sandstone formations of the Garden of the Gods.
@endnode

@node  "CONNECTICUT"
                                  @{u}CONNECTICUT@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Hartford.
POPULATION. 3,281,000.  
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward
            one hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Connecticut offers quiet colonial villages, upmarket `commuter
            towns' for New York executives, lakes, mountains, forests and
            broad sandy beaches. Hartford is the insurance capital of the 
            USA. State attractions include Mark Twains house, Hartford; New
            Haven, home of Yale University and the well known Peabody
            Museum of Natural History; Mystic Seaport, a living museum of
            Whaling; Long Island Sound with it's chain of resort towns and
            fishing ports; and the Gillette Castle Park in Hadlyme.
@endnode 

@node "STATES-D"
    (1) @{"DELAWARE"LINK DELAWARE}
@endnode

@node "DELAWARE"
                                  @{u}DELAWARE@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Dover.
POPULATION. 689,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward 
            one hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Wilmington is this small State's administrative and commercial 
            centre. Founded in 1638, the city includes museums, galleries
            and a port. It's Fort Christina Historic Park is the sight of
            Delaware's first permanent settlement. The rest of the state
            is mostly rural. Attractions include the small capital of city
            Dover; historic New Castle; the fishing town of Lewis;
            Redoboth Beach and Delaware Seashore State Beach.
@endnode

@node "STATES-F"
    (1) @{"FLORIDA"LINK FLORIDA}
@endnode                             

@node "FLORIDA"    
                                  @{u}FLORIDA@{uu}

CAPITAL.    Tallahassee.
POPULATION. 13,488,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 Daylight saving time is observed in the greater part of
            the state - from thee first Sunday in April to the last Sunday
            in October. Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200
            hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Once an ancient Indian homeland, The Florida peninsula now
            offers everything from serene and simple seclusion in the sun
            to luxurious high-life. The State is one of the countries
            leading tourist regions, with winding waterways, freshwater
            lakes, hills, forests, swamps, cities, 13560 km (8426 miles)
            of coast, countless bays, inlets and islands and a legendary
            climate, On it's southeastern tip are Miami and Miami Beach,
            famous and glamorous resorts where the sun shines all year
            long. Florida's greatest expanse of beach, the Miracle Strip
            stretching from Apalachicola to Enascola on the Northeast
            coast, offers more than 160 km (100 miles) of pure white and
            often deserted sand. Then there are the 45 km (28 miles) of
            soft, sandy beaches along the Pinellas Suncoast near Tampa,
            fantasy fun at Walt Disney world, the kennedy Space Centre
            and much, much more.
            USA gateways @{"FLORIDA-GATEWAY" LINK FLORIDA-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "FLORIDA-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}FLORIDA GATEWAY@{uu}


Florida including Miami, Tampa and Orlando, gateways to the southern
States of Georgia and Alabama, as well as central and South America and
the Caribbean.

CLIMATE: The climate is influenced by the adjacent Atlantic Ocean, which
has the effect of slightly lowering temperatures in summer. It has more
thunderstorms than any other State in the USA the area is also affected by
hurricanes or less severe tropical storms, which accounts for heavy
rainfall during the months of July to October. Winters are Mild.

CLOTHING: Lighweight cotton cloths and rainwear. Protective clothing
against the midday sun (such as sunglasses, sun hats and long sleeves) is
advisable in summer. Beachwear is popular.

AIR TRAVEL: From Miami to London is 8 hours 10 minutes. From Tampa to
London is 11 hours 35 minutes (including stopover). From Orlando to London
is 12 hours (including stopover). Plus USA internal domestic flights to
all major cities.
@endnode

@node "STATES-G"
    (1) @{"GEORGIA" LINK GEORGIA} 
@endnode

@node "GEORGIA"

                                  @{u}GEORGIA@{uu}

           
CAPITAL.    Atlanta.
POPULATION. 6,488,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight time is observed from the first Sunday in April
            to the last Sunday in October. Clocks are put forward one
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Georgia founded in 1732, is the youngest of the 13 original
            colonies. It is a mixture of the Old and New South, and is
            geographically diverse, with landscapes ranging from mountains
            in the northeast to the mysterious low-lying Okefenokee Swamp
            in the south, called the land of the `trembling earth' by the
            region's Indian tribes. It's varied climate ranges from the
            low humidity of the blue ridge mountains to the subtropical
            southern coastal region.
            USA Gateways @{"GEORGIA-GATEWAY" LINK GEORGIA-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "GEORGIA-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}GEORGIA GATEWAY@{uu}


Georgia including Atlanta, gateway to the southern Atlantic States of
Georgia, North Carolina and South Carolina, and the southern States of
Alabama, Tennessee and Kentucky.

CLIMATE: Humid and hot in the summer. Frequent rain. Mild winters, cooler
in the northern mountains.

CLOTHING: Lightweight cotton cloths and rain-wear. Warmer clothing foe
evenings, the winter season and mountain areas.

AIR TRAVEL: From Atlanta to London is 9 hours 15 minutes. Plus USA
internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node "STATES-H"
    (1) @{"HAWAII" LINK HAWAII}
@endnode

@node "HAWAII"
                                  @{u}HAWAII@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Honolulu.
POPULATION. 1,067,000.
LOCATION.   3862 km (2400 miles) in the Pacific Ocean off the American
            Pacific east coast. 
TIME.       GMT-10 daylight saving is not observed in the Hawaiian
            Islands.
THE STATE.  The island group of of Hawaii comprises over 200 islands and
            atolls of which seven are inhabited and make up the State
            itself. Oahu contains the capital Honolulu, and is the most
            commercialized, while Hawaii is the biggest island. The
            islands are a less wild version of Polynesia. Oahu has two
            diagonal mountain ranges (The Wainae and Koolau), with many
            beautiful waterfalls. Hawaii is cloaked in orchards and
            bordered by sheer cliffs. The many volcanoes on Hawaii are
            almost without vegetation. The islands support rainforest and
            green flatlands.
            USA Gateways @{"HAWAII-GATEWAY" LINK HAWAII-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "HAWAII-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}HAWAII GATEWAY@{uu}


Hawaii including Honolulu gateway to the Pacific islands.

CLIMATE: Warm throughout the year with some heavy rainfall from December
to March.

CLOTHING: Lightweights are advised throughout the year, with warmer cloths
for winter. Beachwear is popular and protection from the midday sun is
advisable.

AIR TRAVEL: From Honolulu to Anchorage is 5 hours 40 minutes. To Chicago
is 9 hours 55 minutes. To London is 17-19 hours including stopover
depending which route is taken. To Los Angeles 5 hours 20 minutes. To
Miami is 10 hours 35 minutes. To New York is 11 hours 40 minutes. To San
Francisco is 5 hours 5 minutes. And to Washington DC is 11 hours.
@endnode

@node "STATES-I"
    (1) @{"IDAHO" LINK IDAHO}
    (2) @{"ILLINOIS" LINK ILLINOIS}
    (3) @{"INDIANA" LINK INDIANA}
    (4) @{"IOWA" LINK IOWA}
@endnode

@node "IDAHO"
                                  @{u}IDAHO@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Boise.
POPULATION. 1,067,000.
LOCATION.   Western United States.
TIME.       GMT-7 daylight saving is observed in the greater part of the
            State from the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday in
            October Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 hrs 
            local time.
THE STATE.  Idaho includes Hell's Canyon, the deepest in North America;
            the largest stand of white pine in the world at Clearwater
            National Forest; and two of the finest big-game hunting areas
            in the USA - Chamberlain Basin and Selway. Boise hosts a
            summer festival and the August Idaho State Fair. The well-
            known Sun Valley resort area offers skiing and winter sports
            and a range of summer activities. Other attractions include
            the massive Shoshone Falls; the Shoshone Indian Ice Caves;
            historic Fort Hall; the Craters of the Moon National Monument
            area; the Cote d'Alene mining district; and the Nez Perce
            National Historical Park.
@endnode
 
@node "ILLINOIS"
                                  @{u}IILINOIS@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Springfield.
POPULATION  11,631,000.
LOCATION.   Mid to east United States.             
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed in the greater part of the
            State from the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday in
            October Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 hrs 
            local time.
THE STATE.  Illinois, stretching from Lake Michigan to the Mississippi
            River, embraces vast, rich farmlands, the giant City of 
            Chicago rolling glacial plains and, to the south the hills 
            and valleys of the Illinois Ozarks. Abraham Lincoln the 16th
            US President spent most of his professional (he was a lawyer) 
            and political life there.
            USA Gateways @{"ILLINOIS-GATEWAY" LINK ILLINOIS-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "ILLINOIS-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}ILLINOIS GATEWAY@{uu}

Illinois including Chicago, gateway to the Great Lakes, the great plains
and the northern Midwest States of Wisconsin, Iowa, Missouri, Kentucky 
and Indiana.

CLIMATE: Wide variation between hot summers and freezing winters,
especially in the north of the State.The highest humidity is in the
summer near the Great Lakes

CLOTHING: Warm winter cloths are needed in the coldest months. Light to
medium-weight are advised for the summer. Rainwear may be useful.

AIR TRAVEL: From Chicago to London is 7 hours 35 minutes. Plus USA
internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node  "INDIANA"
                                  @{u}INDIANA@{uu}
 

CAPITAL.    Indianapolis.
POPULATION. 5,631,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 (in the greater part of the State).
THE STATE.  Indiana bordered by Lake Michigan to the north, features
            lakes, deep valleys, plains, foothills, industrial areas and
            vast farmlands. Indianapolis is a national centre for industry,
            commerce and culture. It's international airport is 8km 
            (5 miles) from the city centre. State attractions include the 
            Indian Dunes National Lakeshore and Park; Amish Acres, a 
            restored 19th-century Amish community at Nappanee; the Conner
            Prairie Pioneer Settlement; the Squire Boone Caves; and Fort
            Wayne, scene of many bloody battles.
@endnode

@node  "IOWA"
                                  @{u}IOWA@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Des Moines.
POPULATION. 2,812,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in 
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one
            hour changing at 0200 hrs local time.     
THE STATE.  Almost 95% of Iowa's gently undulating land is given over to
            agriculture, but it also offers cities, scenic parks and many
            lakes and recreation areas, such as East and West Okoboji,
            Spirit Lake and Clear lake. It's rich cultural heritage is
            shown in thee German, Swiss and Alsation Amana colonies, with
            their many historic sites and museums. Pella reflects it's
            Dutch past in it's tulip fields, customs and architecture.
            Other attractions include the Boone and Scenic Railroad,
            Effigy Mounds Park, with it's relics of ancient Indian culture;
            and Fort Dodge now restored as a museum.
@endnode

@node "STATES-K"
    (1) @{"KANSAS" LINK KANSAS}
    (2) @{"KENTUCKY" LINK KENTUCKY}
@endnode

@node "KANSAS"
                                  @{u}KANSAS@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Topeka.
POPULATION. 2,523,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in 
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one
            hour changing at 0200 hrs local time.     
THE STATE.  At the geographic centre of North America, Kansas is largely
            agricultural, with vast fields of wheat. It boasts many
            monuments to it's Old West past, as well as numerous
            recreation centres, reservoirs, and rivers offering all kinds
            of outdoor pursuits. Attractions include the restored cattle
            town of Dodge City; the Kansas Cosmosphere and Discovery
            Centre in Hutchinson; and the Swedish settlers town of
            Lindborg. Wichita, it's largest city, includes museums, parks,
            and centres for art, music, theatre and sport.
@endnode

@node "KENTUCKY"
                                  @{u}KENTUCKY@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Frankfort.
POPULATION. 3,755,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 (eastern part) GMT-6 (western part) daylight saving is 
            observed from the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday 
            October. Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 hrs 
            local time.
THE STATE.  Kentucky is best known for it's horses, caves, bourbon and
            blue grass music. Lexington is the horse breeding centre and
            many of its surrounding farms welcome visitors on free tours.
            Louisville boasts the Famous Kentucky Derby, along with
            historic building, top arts venues, a space museum and
            steamboat trips. Other attractions include the Fort Knox gold
            bullion; the pioneer town at Kentucky Lake, one of the largest
            man-made lakes in the world; the Daniel Boone National Forest;
            and Bardtown the `bourbon capital of the world'.
@endnode 
                            
@node "STATES-L"
    (1) @{"LOUISIANA" LINK LOUISIANA}
@endnode

@node "LOUISIANA"
                                  @{u}LOUISIANA@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Baton Rouge
POPULATION. 4,287,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.             
THE STATE.  Louisiana's marshy Mississippi valley is one of the most
            attractive areas of the USA. New Orleans its largest city, is
            one of the countries major tourist attractions. It is famed
            for Dixieland jazz, it's architecture, superb cuisine ant its
            unique French quarter. The city also boasts a wide choice of
            museums and galleries. Other places to see in the state
            include Lafayette, a city of magnificent gardens and the start
            of the 40 km (25 Mile) Azalea trail; the atchafalaya Basin,
            the largest and remote swamp in the USA; the huge salt domes
            of Avery and Jefferson Islands; the Alexandria, surrounded by
            forests and parks; and Hot Wells resort and spa. The 138 mtr
            (452 ft) high marble Capitol Building is situated in Baton
            Rouge.
            USA Gateways @{"LOUISIANA-GATEWAY" LINK LOUISIANA-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "LOUISIANA-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}LOUISIANA GATEWAY@{uu}


Louisiana including New Orleans, gateway to the southern States of
Mississippi and Arkansas.

CLIMATE: Humid and subtropical. Hot temperatures in summer, Mild
temperatures in the spring and autumn and colder in the winter.

CLOTHING: Lighweight cotton clothing for summer, with sweaters and
jackets for winter. Rainwear and umbrella is advised for all seasons.

AIR TRAVEL: New Orleans to Atlanta is 30 minutes, to Chicago is 1 hour,
to Los Angeles is 4 hours, to Miami is 1 hour and to New York is 2
hours. Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node "STATES-M"
    (1) @{"MAINE" LINK MAINE}
    (2) @{"MARYLAND" LINK MARYLAND} 
    (3) @{"MASSACHUSETTS" LINK MASSACHUSETTS}
    (4) @{"MICHIGAN" LINK MICHIGAN}
    (5) @{"MINNESOTA" LINK MINNESOTA}
    (6) @{"MISSISSIPPI" LINK MISSISSIPPI}
    (7) @{"MISSOURI" LINK MISSOURI}
    (8) @{"MONTANA" LINK MONTANA}
@endnode  

@node "MAINE"
                                  @{u}MAINE@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Augusta.
POPULATION. 1,235,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.    

THE STATE.  Maine offers some of the most beautiful scenery in the north.
            about four-fifths of its area forested, but it also includes
            more than 2200 lakes, together with mountains, valleys and 
            seashore. Bangor is a major financial and commercial and
            cultural centre. Portland, Maines largest city, features a
            renovated old port section. Other State attractions include
            the Arcadia National Park on the Atlantic Ocean, one of the 
            most beautiful in the USA; Kittery, the State's oldest town;
            and Kennebunkport, one of the prime beauty spots on the north 
            coast.
@endnode

@node "MARYLAND"
                                  @{u}MARYLAND@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Annapolis.
POPULATION. 4.908,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.  
THE STATE.  Maryland was one of the original 13 States of the USA. Founded
            by Lord Baltimore in 1634 its Atlantic Plain divided by
            Chesapeake Bay rises through the rolling hills and scenic
            farmland of the State's heart-land to the Allegheny Mountains
            of the northwest. Its Tourist destinations range from the 16
            km (10 miles) of white sandy beaches at Ocean City to
            Baltimore's bustling inner harbour, located on Chesapeake Bay;
            it's 6437 km (4000 miles) of shoreline, including its
            tributaries, separate the eastern shore area of Maryland from
            the rest of the State. The twin-spanned Chesapeake Bay Bridge
            11.6 km (7.3 miles) across, is the major link between the two
            sections. Maryland is also the `bridge' linking Baltimore and
            Washington DC. The distance between the two is only 64 km (40
            miles). USA GATEWAYS @{"MARYLAND-GATEWAY" LINK MARYLAND-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "MARYLAND-GATEWAY"
                                  @{u}MARYLAND GATEWAY@{uu}


Maryland including Baltimore, gateway to the northeast Atlantic States
of Delaware and Virginia and the inland States of West Virginia and
Pennsylvania.

CLIMATE: Hot,damp summers and mild, damp winters.

CLOTHING: Lightweight cotton clothing for summer, with jackets and
sweaters and jackets for winter. Rainwear or an umbrella is advised for
all seasons.

AIR TRAVEL: From Baltimore to London is 7 hours 40 minutes (direct).
Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode 

