THE STATE.  Massachusetts was the destination of the Mayflower in 1620
            and is one of the original 13 States. It is now a major
            manufacturing State, offering everything from cobblestoned
            streets and village greens to space-age technology centres.
            The Berkshire Hills cut across its western corner. To the east
            the land rolls down to the sea, embracing the State capital,
            Boston, and the beaches of Cape Cod national Seashore. The two
            regions are connected by the Connecticut River Valley.
