THE STATE.  Michigan comprises two peninsulas. These are divided by Lake
            Michigan, and linked by one of the world's longest suspension
            bridge across the straits of Mackinac. Lakes Superior, Huron
            and Erie also form the States shorelines. The lower peninsula,
            mainly agricultural and industrial, contains inland lakes,
            meadows and sandy beaches as well as the `Motor City' Detroit.
            The upper peninsular is more rugged, and boasts forests, white
            beaches, trout streams and winter ski resorts.
            USA Gateways @{"MICHIGAN-GATEWAY" LINK MICHIGAN-GATEWAY}
@endnode

