Michigan including Detroit, gateway to the Great Lakes and the Midwest.

CLIMATE: Summers are warm with cool nights. Winters are cold, especially
around the Great lakes where conditions can be severe(however, there are
good conditions for winter sports).

CLOTHING: Lighweight cotton clothing for summer, with sweaters and
jackets for winter. Rainwear and umbrella is advised for all seasons.

AIR TRAVEL: Detroit to London is 7 hours 10 minutes.
Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node "MINNESOTA"
