            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
THE STATE.  Mississippi is noted for its pre-Civil war mansions, fine
            beaches and scenery. More the 16,000 acres have been set aside
            for camping and recreation, including the Clarbco and Percy
            Quinn State parks. National forests include Bienville, DeSoto,
            Delta and Holly Springs, famed for its restored country houses.
            Natchez, with fine 18th and 19th century architecture, is near
            the start of the restored Natchez Trace Trail to Nashville.
            The route passes the ancient Indian Emerald Mound and ghost 
            town of Rocky Springs. Other attractions include Vickburg,
            with its national military park; on the state's beach-lined
            border with the Gulf of Mexico.
          
@endnode

@node "MISSOURI"
                                  @{u}MISSOURI@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Jefferson City.
POPULATION. 5.193,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.     
THE STATE.  Missouri,in the heart of the USA, is a blend of frontier West, 
            gracious South, the sophisticated East and industrial North.
            The Missouri valley was a major pioneer route, with St Louis
            known as the `Gateway to the west'. It is bounded by the
            Mississippi River in the east. Prairies lie in the north of
            the Missouri, the longest river in the USA, with great plains
            to the west, rolling hills in the south and the Mississippi
            cotton lands to the southeast. It's riverboat culture was
            immortalised by Mark twain in `Life on the Mississippi' and
            his tales of Tom sawyer and Huckleberry Finn.
            USA gateways @{"MISSOURI-GATEWAY" LINK MISSOURI-GATEWAY}
@endnode        

