New Jersey including Newark, gateway to the North Atlantic states of New
Jersey, New York and Maryland and the northeastern State of Pennsylvania.

CLIMATE:  The climate is changeable with moderate rainfall throughout the
year. During the summer heatwaves are common, with temperatures staying at
over 73°C for several days.

CLOTHING: Lighweight cotton clothing for summer, with sweaters and
jackets for winter.

AIR TRAVEL: New Jersey to London is 6 hours 50 minutes. 3 hours 50 minutes
by Concorde. Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
