THE STATE.  Ohio, birthplace of seven US presidents, is an expanse of
            fertile farmland dotted with industrial centres. Cleveland,
            on the shores of Lake Erie, is a major industrial city with
            many tourist attractions, including a museum, planetarium, and
            the University Circle of performing arts venues and galleries.
            Cincinnati, on the Ohio River also boasts sightseeing and
            cultural attractions. The Greater Cincinnati and Cleveland
            Hopkins international airports are nearby. Other places of
            interest include Cedar Point beach resort on Lake Erie;
            Seaworld in Aurora; the peaceful Lake Erie Islands; and the 
            scenic hocking Hills area around Logan.
@endnode

