LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.  
THE STATE.  Oklahoma comprises mountains, forests and lakes to the east,
            plains and farmland in the centre, and wide-open ranching
            country to the west. It is the home to more Indian Tribes than
            any other state in the USA. Oklahoma City offers many tourist
            attractions, including The Western Heritage Centre and
            operating oil wells. Tulsa also has an international airport
            and boasts some of the west's major art centres and galleries.
            State park resorts and recreation areas include Eufaula Lake;
            Lake Texom; Arrowhead; Quarts Mountain; and Western Hills. 
            Indian City USA and the Cherokee Heritage Centre recreate the
            Indian life of centuries ago.
@endnode

