            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.   
THE STATE.  Oregon has many areas of great natural beauty and boasts more
            than 230 State Parks and hundreds of camping areas in 13
            national forests. Portland, the `City of Roses', boasts fine 
            gardens, restaurants, shops, concerts, jazz festivals and
            theatres. Its international airport is 14 km (9 miles) east of
            downtown salem. State tourist destinations include the
            spectacular coast north of the California border; historic
            Astoria on the Columbia River; the Sea Lion caves; Mount Hood
            Forest; Crater Lake park; 19th-century Jacksonville; the
            Oregon Cave and Hells Canyon.
@endnode
  
