            observed from the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday 
            October. Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 hrs 
            local time.   
THE STATE.  South Dakota includes the dramatic Badlands, fertile prairies,
            early pioneer towns and the Black Hills, with forests, lakes,
            caves. By far the biggest tourist attraction is the Mount
            Rushmore Memorial, where the faces of four American presidents
            have been blasted and carved out of the mountain. Sioux Falls
            and Rapid City are gateways to the area and have good air
            connections. State attractions include The black Hills
            National Forest; The Badlands national Park; and the Wind Cave
            National Park. All offers a host of outdoor pursuits.
@endnode

@node "STATES-T"
    (1) @{"TENNESSEE" LINK TENNESSEE}
    (2) @{"TEXAS" LINK TEXAS}
@endnode
    
@node "TENNESSEE"
                                  @{u}TENNESSEE@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Nashville.
POPULATION. 5,024,000.
LOCATION.   Mid-east United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
THE STATE.  More than half of Tennessee is forested and great tracts have
            have been set aside as State and national parks, forests,
            wilderness areas and game reserves. Nasville is a major music
            performance and recording centre. It also boasts a host of
            fine colleges and churches, a full-size replica of the
            Parthenon, the County Music Hall of Fame and the Opreyland USA
            music entertainment complex. Memphis, the State's largest City,
            is a major trading centre. Its major tourist attraction is
            Graceland, the home of the late Elvis Presley, and famous
            Beale Street is featured in many blues songs. At Chattanooga,
            take a ride up Lookout mountain, with its Rock City Gardens
            and Ruby Falls. Gatlingburg is the starting point for trips
            into the Great Smoky Mountain National Park.
@endnode

@node "TEXAS"
                                  @{u}TEXAS@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Austin.
POPULATION. 17,656,000.
LOCATION.   Middle United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed in the Greater part of the
            State - from the first Sunday in April to the last Sunday 
            October. Clocks are put forward one hour, changing at 0200 
            hrs local time.      
THE STATE.  Big, bold and colourful, the `Lone Star State' is the second
            largest in the USA, covering more than 431 sq km (262,017 sq
            miles). Spain was the first European power to lay claim to
            Texas; it also flew the flags of France and Mexico before
            gaining its independence in 1836. It was granted US statehood
            in 1846. Texas borders Mexico along the Rio Grande and
            embraces vast mountain ranges and canyons to the west; lakes;
            plantations and pine forests to the east; broad plains to the
            north; citrus groves, Gulf of Mexico beaches and low-lying
            alluvial plains to the south; and emerald hill country and
            clear springs at its heart. Its great wealth stems from its
            vast oil reserves. It has several booming cities; Houston, 
            Dallas, Fort Worth, San Antonio, El Paso and its capital city 
            Austin. USA Gateway @{"TEXAS-GATEWAY" LINK TEXAS-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "TEXAS-GATEWAY"
                             @{u}TEXAS GATEWAY@{uu}


Texas including Dallas/Fort Worth and Houston, gateways to the southwest
States of New Mexico, Oklahoma, Arkansas and Louisiana.

CLIMATE: Dry and warm to very hot throughout the year. Occasional freak
rainstorms.

CLOTHING: Lightweights throughout most of the year and warmer during
winter.

AIR TRAVEL: Dallas/Fort Worth to London is 11 hours (including stopover).
Houston to London is 10 hours 15 minutes. Plus USA internal domestic 
flights to all major cities.
@endnode

@node "STATES-U"
    (1) @{"UTAH" LINK UTAH}
@endnode

@node "UTAH"
                                  @{u}UTAH@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Salt Lake City.
POPULATION. 1,813,000.
LOCATION.   Western United States.
TIME.       GMT-7 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.  
THE STATE.  Utah's attractions include canyons, colourful towns, and 
            breathtaking national parks. Salt Lake City, with its
            international airport 11 km (7 miles) west of downtown, is the
            world centre of the Mormon Church. Utah, surrounded bt the
            Wasatch Mountains, boasts historic buildings, churches,
            museums, science exhibitions and art festivals. Other State
            attractions include Zion National Park around the Virgin River
            Canyon, with its temple-like rock formations; Canyonlands,
            Arches and Capital Reef National Park; and Timpanogos Cave and
            Dinosaur national Monument near Vernal.
@endnode

@node "STATES-V"
    (1) @{"VERMONT" LINK VERMONT}
    (2) @{"VIRGINIA" LINK VIRGINIA}
@endnode

@node "VERMONT"
                                  @{u}VERMONT@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Montpelier.
POPULATION. 570,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
THE STATE.  Vermont is the only new England State without a seashore, but
            its border with Lake Champlain more than compensates, its
            largest city, Burlington affords magnificent views of the
            water, with its many sporting and recreation areas. The State's
            attractions include Stowe, the famous ski resort on the slopes
            of Mount Mansfield; Heritage Park, with its early new England
            buildings; and Green Mountain National Forest, with its
            historical trails and drives. Other major ski areas include 
            Killington, Sugarbush, Mount Snow, jay Peak, Smugglers Notch
            and Haystack.
@endnode

@node "VIRGINIA"
                                  @{u}VIRGINIA@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Richmond.
POPULATION. 5,136,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
THE STATE.  Virginia is one of the country's most historic and scenic
            States. Some of its leading attractions are located along the
            Potomac River - Arlington National Cemetery, with the grave of
            John F kennedy; Old Town Alexandria; and Mount Vernon. George
            Washington's country estate. Richmond the capital of the
            Confederacy in the Civil War, has many fine buildings.
            Williamsburg, Yorktown, and Jamestown, the birthplace of the
            USA and three of its most historic sites, are situated further
            east. Shenandoah Valley, with its caverns, waterfalls, and
            popular resorts, is to the west. Other attractions include
            Virginia Beach resort; Cumberland Gap; and the Great Falls
            Park. Norfolk is an important Atlantic seaport.
@endnode

@node "STATES-W"
    (1) @{"WASHINGTON" LINK WASHINGTON}
    (2) @{"WEST-VIRGINIA" LINK WEST-VIRGINIA}
    (3) @{"WISCONSIN" LINK WISCONSIN}
    (4) @{"WYOMING" LINK WYOMING}
@endnode

@node "WASHINGTON"

                                  @{u}WASHINGTON@{uu}



CAPITAL.    Olympia.
POPULATION. 5,136,000.
LOCATION.   West United States.
TIME.       GMT-8 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
THE STATE.  Washington State, bordering Canada and the Pacific Ocean,
            offers some of the nation's finest scenery for outdoor
            recreation. It has the second-highest population of any western
            State, yet visitors can travel from any city centre to
            peaceful countryside within minutes. The Snake and Columbia
            rivers flow through eastern Washington State before joining
            to cut a passage through the Cascades, the north-south
            mountain range that dominates the centre of the State, rising
            to 4392 km (14,408 ft) at mount Rainer. There are many fine 
            beaches and small resorts on the Pacific coast. Much of the
            State is covered by coniferous forest. Holiday highlights
            include yachting on Puget Sound, hiking along the Pacific
            Crest National Scenic Trail and mountain climbing in the
            Cascades and Olympics. Excellent accommodation is available,
            ranging from bed and breakfast establishments to 5-star
            luxury hotels. USA Gateway @{"WASHINGTON-STATE-GATEWAY" LINK
WASHINGTON-STATE-GATEWAY}
@endnode

@node "WASHINGTON-STATE-GATEWAY"
                                  @{u}WASHINGTON STATE GATEWAY@{uu}


Washington State including Seattle, gateway to the Pacific northwest
States of Washington,, Oregon, Idaho and Alaska.

CLIMATE: Washington has two distinct climate zones. Summer days west of
the Cascades rarely rise above 26°C, and winter days seldom drop below
8°C. While the east of the State has warm summers and cool winters.

CLOTHING. Hard to say depends which part of the State you wish to visit.

AIR TRAVEL: Seattle to London is 9 hours 5 minutes (direct).
Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode 

@node  "WEST-VIRGINIA"
                                  @{u}WEST VIRGINIA@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Charleston.
POPULATION. 1,812,000.
LOCATION.   Eastern United states.
TIME.       GMT-5 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Monongahela National Forest occupies a vast area in the eastern
            part of this mountain State and includes the Spruce Knob-Seneca
            Rocks National Recreation Area. West Virginia also boasts some
            of the nation's best State parks, with good sports and
            recreation facilities. These include Bluestone and Pipstern.
            Other attractions include the Greenbrier luxury resort; Smoke
            Hole Scenic Gorge; Mammoth Mound, one of the world's tallest
            prehistoric Indian burial grounds; and the State Capital in
            Charleton, on of the best Italian Renaissance buildings in the 
            USA.
@endnode

@node "WISCONSIN"
                                  @{u}WISCONSIN@{uu}


CAPITAL.    Madison.
POPULATION. 5,007,000.
LOCATION.   Mid-eastern United States.
TIME.       GMT-6 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time.
THE STATE.  Wisconsin has more than 15,000 lakes and thousands of
            kilometres of rivers and streams. Its varied countryside also
            includes sandstone cliffs, sandy beaches, northern forests and
            rich southern farmland. Milwaukee is the State's largest city,
            on the shores of Lake Michigan. it is well known for its
            German heritage, top performance arts companies and fin
            restaurants. Its parks and museums are among the best in the
            USA. Other State attractions include the sculptured cliffs of
            the Wisconsin Dells; Lake Geneva, a favourite recreation spot;
            and Green Bay, the States oldest settlement.
@endnode

@node "WYOMING"
                                  @{u}WYOMING@{uu}
CAPITAL.    Cheyenne.
POPULATION. 466,000.
LOCATION.   Mid-west United States.
TIME.       GMT-7 daylight saving is observed from the first Sunday in
            April to the last Sunday October. Clocks are put forward one 
            hour, changing at 0200 hrs local time. 
 THE STATE. Wyoming the `Cowboy State', boasts 11 major mountain ranges,
            prairies, grasslands, parks, forests, lakes and rivers. The
            huge Yellowstone national Park includes geysers, hot springs,
            canyons, mountain lakes, waterfalls and a huge variety of
            wildlife. Old Faithful Geyser, the park's most famous
            attraction, erupts almost hourly. Other state attractions
            include Grand Teton National Park; Devil's Tower, the core of
            a now extinct volcano; the Buffalo Bill Historical Centre in
            Cody; Fort Laramie pioneer post; Bighorn Canyon; and Prior
            Mountain Wild Horse Range, with more than 200 free roaming 
            wild horses.
@endnode

@node "USA-CAPITAL"
                                  @{u}USA CAPITAL@{uu}


The Capital of the United States is Washington in the District of Columbia.
It is not a State the only part of District of Columbia is in fact
Washington, lying adjacent to the river Potomac.
USA Gateway @{"WASHINGTON-DC-GATEWAY" LINK WASHINGTON-DC-GATEWAY}
@endnode
 
@node "WASHINGTON-DC-GATEWAY"

                                  @{u}WASHINGTON DC GATEWAY@{uu}


Washington DC including gateway to George Washington Country, including
Pennsylvania, Maryland, Delaware, Virginia and West Virginia.

CLIMATE: Summers are very warm while winter temperatures can be very low.

CLOTHING: Lighweight cotton clothing for summer, with sweaters and
jackets for winter. 

AIR TRAVEL: Washington DC to London is 6 hours 50 minutes.
Plus USA internal domestic flights to all major cities.
@endnode

